The paper deals with the application of machine learning and data mining methods for cyber security, specifically for intrusion detection. This falls under the category of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of dimensionality reduction and rule extraction, which are techniques commonly used in "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) and "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of unsupervised anomaly detection, which is a topic in "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI).
